rComments: Class was so boring. If you can't teach yourself the material, then you will do poorly. He always gooes off of the topic and you can easily get confused about what he is talking about.
If you can teach yourself, class isn't that bad. huge curve at the end. lecture is pointless if you know how to read the textbook.

He was such a sweet old man but his teaching methods weren't very effective. Stick to the book. The TA's for the class make the material much easier to understand. Lectures are a waste of time but he gives pop quizzes so you still have to go. Make it mandatory to go the discussions and you'll be fine.
His Lectures are a complete waste of time. He wrote the book, stick to that. Everything else is just going through the motions.
blah. most boring lectures ever
This class was cake. Tests are just like old ones. Just memorized/understand those concepts and you're guarenteed an A.

Goes off topic a lot with stories, etc., not intersting, not immersive, and does not "teach"  Even talking to him in office hours he is just very into a separate sort of world.  The way the exams are graded is very subjective, and you really have to rely on yourself for this one.  Better off transfering credit.
Lectures are pretty ineffective, especially at 9am. Just read the book and understand the material thoroughly and the class wont be hard.

The problem with the exams isn't just that they're "hard"- it's that they're extremely vague. You WILL be deducted points for failing to provide graphs you weren't asked to draw and defining terms that you weren't asked to define. If you want to do well, you better provide EVERY POSSIBLE piece of information, no matter how unneccessary it may seem.

I don't get what everyone's big deal is about Gottheil and ripping on him. I used to be like most of you guys thinking he was a bad teacher but he knows his stuff better than a lot of teachers. And people complain that his tests are so hard. God forbid you read the book and write coherent answers...Anyways, this class isn't bad if you're not LAZY

Terrible teacher. (and I use "teacher" loosely). Doesn't explain actual subject in lecture. How well you do would depend on your TA I guess, but mine barely spoke English. HARD tests and random pop quizzes. Nightmare of a class

Pop quizzes aren't worth waking up for, professor and TAs don't explain topics in anywhere near the amount of depth they're going to want you to explain it in on the exam. For the record, they post the old exams and the midterm and final for this semester have been MUCH MORE difficult than past years.
SO awful. Gottheil doesn't explain ANYTHING in lecture except for his obsession for fish. Lecture is completely worthless.
ad

Worst professor I have had at this university by far.  Tests are 100% and grading is absolutely ridiculous in every facet.  Anyone notice that he didn't pass out ICES forms at the end of the course? I wonder why....
his lecture was worthless and his tests were imosssible.  Essay tests for the midterm and final....come on!

This man is one of the worst lecturers ever.  Nothing puts you to sleep like a morning lecture with him.  His pop quizes are vindictive, he gives them when he is not happy with attendance.  Forces you to learn material for the tests by chapter number, citing chapter 3 is going to be really useful later in life.  He should be terminated ASAP!!!!!!!!
He doesn't deserve to be a professor!

The course material is somewhat interesting, and the professor makes the material seem very easy and second-nature.  The problem with this course are the ridiculously difficult midterm and final examinations, on which appear questions that are never once referenced in the course.  This professor is arrogant and stuck in an Ivory Tower.
